article.headline: Illinois 58, Iowa 47
article.story: IOWA CITY, Iowa (AP)Shaun Pruitt scored 18 points as Illinois defeated Iowa 58-47 Saturday. The Illini went on a 16-5 run midway through the first half to take control of the game and never looked back. Illinois (12-17, 4-12 Big Ten) led by as many as 11 during the second half. Iowa (12-18, 5-12) pulled to within five at 45-40 on a Tony Freeman free throw with 6:11 remaining, but Travis Meacham sank a 3-pointer to push Illinois' lead to eight. Freeman again brought Iowa to within five on a three-point play with 2:21 remaining, but the Hawkeyes would get no closer. Shaun Pruitt got credit for a basket on a goal tending call, and Meacham added a pair of free throws to stretch Illinois' lead to nine. The Illini sank their last six free throws to put the game away. Freeman led Iowa with 21 points.
